This paper deals with a machine learning problem of multi-view subspace learning, which involves finding a low-dimensional subspace of data obtained from multiple views. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on modeling noise in multi-view data, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, which deal with machine learning and computer vision, respectively. The other sub-categories are also relevant but less likely to be the primary focus of the paper.
